.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.SS to\-uefi
.PP
.I Convert BIOS/MBR system to UEFI/GPT
.PP
.B Category:
Migration
.br
.B Maturity:
stable
.PP
.B SYNTAX
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
lamboot\-migrate to\-uefi [\-\-disk DEV] [\-\-esp\-size MB] [\-\-bootloader NAME] [\-\-method A|B|C|auto] [\-\-cmdline STR] [\-\-backup\-dir PATH] [\-\-skip\-verify] [\-\-keep\-legacy\-mbr]
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B ARGUMENTS
.PP
.RS 4
.TP
.B \-\-disk DEV
Target disk (default: auto\-detect root disk)
.TP
.B \-\-esp\-size MB
ESP partition size in MB (default: 550)
.TP
.B \-\-bootloader NAME
grub\-efi (default), lamboot, or systemd\-boot
.TP
.B \-\-method A
\-\-method A
.TP
.B B
B
.TP
.B C
C
.TP
.B auto
Proxmox VM method selector (default: auto)
.TP
.B \-\-cmdline STR
Override kernel cmdline for new BLS entries
.TP
.B \-\-backup\-dir PATH
Where to store the backup (default: /var/backups/lamboot\-migrate\-<ts>/)
.TP
.B \-\-skip\-verify
Don\'t run verification suite after conversion
.TP
.B \-\-keep\-legacy\-mbr
Leave MBR boot code (protective) — default
.RE
.PP
.B EXAMPLES
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
sudo lamboot\-migrate to\-uefi \-\-disk /dev/sda
sudo lamboot\-migrate to\-uefi \-\-dry\-run
sudo lamboot\-migrate to\-uefi \-\-bootloader lamboot \-\-esp\-size 1024
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B NOTES
.PP
.RS 4
Runs a 10\-phase pipeline with safety gates at each step. The first 6 phases are reversible with no disk changes (rollback runs a diff). After Phase 4 (MBR→GPT), rollback requires the backup dir. Always back up your system before running. For boot disk migration on physical hardware, run from live media.
.RE
.PP
.B OFFLINE:
No \- requires online system
.br
.B PRIVILEGE:
Requires root (sudo)
.PP
.B SEE ALSO
.PP
.RS 4
to\-lamboot, verify, rollback, status
.RE
.PP
.B DOCUMENTATION URL
.PP
.RS 4
.UR https://lamboot.dev/tools/migrate/to-uefi
.UE
.RE
.PP
.SS to\-lamboot
.PP
.I Migrate UEFI system from another bootloader to LamBoot
.PP
.B Category:
Migration
.br
.B Maturity:
stable
.PP
.B SYNTAX
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
lamboot\-migrate to\-lamboot [\-\-esp PATH] [\-\-preserve\-grub|\-\-remove\-grub] [\-\-force]
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B ARGUMENTS
.PP
.RS 4
.TP
.B \-\-esp PATH
ESP mount point (default: auto\-detect)
.TP
.B \-\-preserve\-grub
Keep existing bootloader as fallback (default)
.TP
.B \-\-remove\-grub
Remove GRUB packages + ESP files + NVRAM entries after verify passes (DANGEROUS)
.TP
.B \-\-force
Skip typed\-yes confirmation when \-\-remove\-grub is used
.RE
.PP
.B EXAMPLES
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
sudo lamboot\-migrate to\-lamboot
sudo lamboot\-migrate to\-lamboot \-\-preserve\-grub
sudo lamboot\-migrate to\-lamboot \-\-remove\-grub    # asks for confirmation
sudo lamboot\-migrate to\-lamboot \-\-remove\-grub \-\-force
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B NOTES
.PP
.RS 4
Invokes lamboot\-install. With \-\-preserve\-grub (default) the prior bootloader stays as a UEFI fallback. With \-\-remove\-grub the tool runs verify first; if all 11 checks pass, it uninstalls the distro\'s GRUB packages, removes GRUB files from the ESP, and deletes GRUB Boot#### entries from NVRAM. Refuses to remove if verify fails. Requires typed\-yes confirmation unless \-\-force.
.RE
.PP
.B OFFLINE:
No \- requires online system
.br
.B PRIVILEGE:
Requires root (sudo)
.PP
.B SEE ALSO
.PP
.RS 4
to\-uefi, rollback
.RE
.PP
.B DOCUMENTATION URL
.PP
.RS 4
.UR https://lamboot.dev/tools/migrate/to-lamboot
.UE
