.SS rollback
.PP
.I Revert the most recent to\-uefi run using its backup
.PP
.B Category:
Recovery
.br
.B Maturity:
stable
.PP
.B SYNTAX
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
lamboot\-migrate rollback [\-\-backup\-dir PATH]
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B ARGUMENTS
.PP
.RS 4
.TP
.B \-\-backup\-dir PATH
Specific backup to restore (default: most recent)
.RE
.PP
.B EXAMPLES
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
sudo lamboot\-migrate rollback
sudo lamboot\-migrate rollback \-\-backup\-dir /var/backups/lamboot\-migrate\-2026\-04\-22...
sudo lamboot\-migrate rollback \-\-dry\-run
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B NOTES
.PP
.RS 4
Restores the original MBR partition table, original fstab, and original /etc/default/grub. Removes the UEFI boot entry created during to\-uefi. You will need to switch firmware back to Legacy/CSM after rollback to boot off the restored MBR.
.RE
.PP
.B OFFLINE:
No \- requires online system
.br
.B PRIVILEGE:
Requires root (sudo)
.PP
.B SEE ALSO
.PP
.RS 4
to\-uefi, verify
.RE
.PP
.B DOCUMENTATION URL
.PP
.RS 4
.UR https://lamboot.dev/tools/migrate/rollback
.UE
